Player: Dungeon Master Note: Resume the game, the player has returned.

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Springmonth 1 13:01:00. Player: len, did you share the icnantation?

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "As you return to the heart of the command post, the spring sunlight slants through the clearing, casting shifting patterns along the battered palisade. The bustle of rangers is momentarily interrupted as your question rings out: 'Elen, did you share the incantation?'\n\nCommander Elen pauses from her vigil over the battered oak table, her gaze steady and thoughtful. She glances at the scrap of parchment Kira retrieved from Sila, then approaches, her tone measured but warm. 'The words needed to attune a new crystal to the West Tower bell?' she asks, voice carrying just enough for Kira and the nearby rangers to hear. 'Aye, I know them. It's a simple blessing, but the ritual must be performed at high noon under clear sky, and the words must be spoken with a steady heart.'\n\nShe leans in, meeting your eyes with the gravity of the moment. 'Repeat after me, Eirik. May the light of dawn break all shadow, may the silver sound carry warning and hope, and may the watch be unbroken from this day forth.'\n\nKira grins, relief softening her shoulders. 'That should do the trick for the crystal. I can almost hear the bell ringing already.'\n\nElen adds quietly, 'You'll need a quartz or enchanted glass for the repair. Trader Sila might still have a fragment left, or you may have luck searching the North Tower's rubble, but you must act quickly. The West Tower's silence leaves our flank exposed.'\n\nThe command post seems to draw a collective breath, waiting for your decision. The knowledge is yours, Eirik. What do you want to do next?",
  "actions": []
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Springmonth 1 13:01:00. Player: Sila didn't have any. Kira, should we check the north tower or head stratigh to the west tower to check for the chest?

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "Kira glances at you, brushing a lock of hair behind her ear as she considers your question, her eyes flicking from the command post's bustle to the battered map on Elen's table.\n\n'If Sila's out of crystals, then the North Tower rubble is our best shot, Eirik. Those quartz veins by the overlook might still have something we can use--even a decent shard could work for the repair.' She pauses, biting her lip. 'But if we want to recover Sila's chest and keep her from leaving, the bandit cache near the West Tower is the place to look.'\n\nShe lowers her voice, thoughtful. 'We could split the difference--search the North Tower for a crystal first, then swing by the West Tower on our way out. Or if you want to move fast and get the chest before any bandits come back for it, we head straight there and risk patching the bell after.'\n\nKira's gaze settles on you, a spark of faith flickering in her expression. 'Your call. Either way, the sooner we move, the better. What do you think, Eirik?'",
  "actions": []
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Springmonth 1 13:01:00. Player: Le's head straight to the chest in case we have time to also save Silas wheres

